convert_h5_to_tflite.py： convert Conv_AE model to tensorflow lite framework
convert_unrolled.py: convert LSTM_AE model to tensorflow lite framework

 Tips:to configure on Platformio, using ini file and main.cpp
use Noise sensor and PM2.5 sensor on ESP32 to detect the noise and PM2.5, then use the following commands on computer to burn in ESP32:

pio run 
pio run -t upload
pio run -t uploadfs
pio device monitor --port COM7 --baud 115200

After following the 4 steps, the ESP32 could run without a computer, only  electricity is enough. 
ESP32 will do the following things automatically:
(1)
ESP32 starts automatically on boot
Read noise data every second
Form a sample every minute
Finalize one hourly feature every hour

Run the model every 10 minutes
(2) Log Fields:
Timestamp
avg_pm25
duration_hour_equiv
event_hour_equiv
avg_salience
mae
anomaly
